.TH mlib_SignalLinear2ALaw 3MLIB "2 Mar 2007" "SunOS 5.11" "mediaLib Library Functions"
.SH NAME
mlib_SignalLinear2ALaw \- ITU G.711 m-law and A-law compression and
decompression
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
.nf
cc [ \fIflag\fR... ] \fIfile\fR... \fB-lmlib\fR [ \fIlibrary\fR... ]
#include <mlib.h>

\fBmlib_status\fR \fBmlib_SignalLinear2ALaw\fR(\fBmlib_u8 *\fIacode\fR,
     \fBconst mlib_s16 *\fIpcm\fR, \fBmlib_s32\fR \fIn\fR);
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
The \fBmlib_SignalLinear2ALaw()\fR function performs ITU G.711 m-law and
A-law compression and decompression in compliance with the ITU (Former
CCITT) G.711 specification.
.SH PARAMETERS
.sp
.LP
The function takes the following arguments:
.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fIacode\fR
.ad
.RS 9n
.rt
A-law code array.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fIpcm\fR
.ad
.RS 9n
.rt
Linear PCM sample array.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fIn\fR
.ad
.RS 9n
.rt
Number of samples in the source array.
.RE

.SH RETURN VALUES
.sp
.LP
The function returns \fBMLIB_SUCCESS\fR if successful. Otherwise it returns
\fBMLIB_FAILURE\fR.
